headline: US Vehicle Auction Market Trends 2025-2030 Featuring Openlane, Copart, ACV, RB Global, E Automotive, eBay, COX Automotive, Capital, Cars & Bids, A Better Bid Car, AutoBidMaster, Barrett-Jackson
summary: The US vehicle auction market was valued at $3.47 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach $4.48 billion by 2030, driven by digital transformation and a steady supply from fleet operators and lease expirations. The market is expected to grow at a CAGR of 4% from 2025-2030, fueled by increased demand for whole cars and a shift towards online auctions. headline: You should consider these 3 stock picks, portfolio manager says
